         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the use of difference methods for weakly nonlinear systems of ordinary differential equations with rapidly oscillating solutions and develop a general approach which depends only on the smoothness of the coefficients and the nonlinearities. In particular, one is led to a strategy which is suitable for the detection and resolution of turning points in such systems. A computational example is presented.</p>
          </abstract>
